body_html: @up-to-you While we're at it, I've also included feature.pb.h, example.pb.h, record_reader.h in commit bytedeco/javacpp-presets@fce6bfb. FYI, while the Java API of protocol buffers are easier to use, serializing and deserializing with the C++ versions might be be faster, especially if the resulting objects are to be used with the C++ API anyway.

body: @up-to-you While we're at it, I've also included `feature.pb.h`, `example.pb.h`, `record_reader.h` in commit https://github.com/bytedeco/javacpp-presets/commit/fce6bfb26ceacb8d7a4cd4ed6651e0f1e1ffc8ac.
